parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause a loss of braking power, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake line failure at the bend where it joins with the rear brake hose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS computer can cause a total loss of brakes, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: failure of the ABS system to function properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty wheel speed sensors can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances or loss of braking power.
Poor brake system design can lead to corrosion-induced brake line failure, ABS computer failure, or faulty wheel speed sensors, causing a loss of braking power or accidents.
The intermittent failure of the windshield wipers can reduce visibility during rainy or snowy conditions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: wipers may or may not come back on

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An inaccurate fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel unexpectedly, leading to engine stalling, loss of power, and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: The fuel gauge displays an incorrect reading
showing more fuel than is actually in the tank
the fuel gauge does not move from a specific position
the fuel gauge does not respond to changes in fuel level.
